  "response_text": "Against a dark, plain background, a round cake covered in thick white frosting fills the center. A tall wire beater or whisk-like utensil hovers above the cake and gradually lifts away, leaving the frosting piled high and textured with broad swirls and ridges. As the utensil disappears upward, the cake is fully revealed on a scalloped serving plate, its sides coated in creamy white icing with hand-smoothed waves.\n\nA drawn cartoon figure appears beside a large Imperial Sugar carton, both placed in front of the frosted cake as if standing on the cake plate. The cartoon character is a smiling, crown-wearing mascot with thin arms and legs and the words “PURE CANE” printed on its body. It gestures proudly toward the carton. The package is labeled “10X Imperial Pure Cane Sugar” and “10X confectioners powdered,” with “Imperial Sugar” also visible near the bottom. The mascot points, opens its arms, and presents the box while the cake remains as the backdrop.\n\nThe image blends into a studio demonstration. A well-dressed adult woman with short curled hair stands behind a table, wearing a dark dress and a light necklace. A carton of Imperial Sugar sits on the table to her left. In front of her is a rectangular frame holding a taut sheet of fine fabric, identified by the accompanying context as silk. She faces forward, poised like a presenter, with the fabric frame positioned between her and the viewer.\n\nThe demonstration moves closer to the table. The Imperial Sugar carton remains upright at the left. The woman’s hands work over the stretched fabric, spreading a mound of white powdered sugar across the top surface. Beneath the fabric is a dark tray or box that makes the falling powder easy to see. As she rubs or sifts the sugar across the silk, a pale stream falls through and collects below, forming a soft white pile on the dark surface. The top layer of sugar thins as she continues moving her hand across the fabric, while the sifted sugar grows underneath.\n\nThe setting changes to a kitchen counter. An adult woman with neatly styled hair stands behind a mixing bowl, wearing a light buttoned blouse with rolled sleeves and a dark skirt or apron. A measuring cup or small container sits to her left, and an Imperial Sugar carton stands to her right. She looks down toward the bowl as if preparing frosting. A close overhead view follows, showing a round bowl filled with very dark, glossy frosting. One hand steadies the bowl while the other stirs with a spoon or spatula. The mixture folds smoothly in thick, shiny waves as it is worked around the bowl, suggesting a rich chocolate frosting.\n\nTwo finished cakes are then displayed on pedestal cake stands against a simple studio background. On the left is a dark frosted cake with a shiny, swirled top, likely chocolate. On the right is a white frosted cake with high, fluffy icing and decorative ridges down the side. The white cake becomes the center of attention, sitting elevated on its stand with its thick frosting piled and smoothed on top.\n\nA young girl appears seated at a table beside the white frosted cake. She has light hair with straight bangs and wears a dark dress with a white rounded collar. The cake sits to her left on its pedestal, and an Imperial Sugar carton stands in front of her to her right. She looks toward the carton and then forward, her mouth opening as if speaking along with the final line. She brings her hands to the package and holds it upright, keeping the “Imperial Sugar” label facing outward. At the end, she smiles gently while holding the carton close, with the white frosted cake still visible beside her.",
